                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7332</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-19T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 19, 1916, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Telegraph present status promised vigorous campaign against Yaqui
                            Indians, and whether settlers in Yaqui Valley are now adequately
                            protected.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
